  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p>Fluoxetine, a heavily prescribed antidepressant marketed under the name Prozac, can be prepared by a route that begins with reaction between a phenol and an alkyl chloride.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbzRYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2d9d103e6ce4e92481f5d554878f7043d4710194/OChem_18_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"4-trifluoromethylphenol reacts with an alkyl chloride with phenyl and amine groups in potassium hydroxide and D M S O to produce fluoxetine through a series of steps.\">",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 361202,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "The rate of the reaction depends on both phenol and alkyl halide. Is this an S<sub>N</sub>1 or an S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction? Show the mechanism.",
